  "title": "Technical Assistant (Shipping)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Work with Managers and Superintendents to arrange technical spare parts, vessel repairs, and annual servicing.</li>\n  <li>Handle purchasing, send enquiries to suppliers, prepare quotations, and issue POs through the accounting system.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate logistics (air, sea, or land transport) to ensure timely delivery of parts to vessels.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with ships and agents on repair and supply arrangements at convenient ports.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and organize all related documents such as invoices, packing lists, and delivery orders.</li>\n  <li>Verify vendor costs, secure necessary approvals, and assist accounts in invoicing.</li>\n  <li>Perform general administrative and documentation duties as required.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma or equivalent qualification.</li>\n  <li>6 months to 1 year of relevant experience in marine, shipping, or repair companies.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
